The cascade palette is a keyboard-driven command surface — a single window into actions, configuration, entities, and search that follows a small set of consistent gestures.

! Four gestures

|!Gesture |!Effect |
|`Ctrl-Space` |Open the palette anywhere. Resets to root if already open. |
|`Tab` or `→` |Drill into the selected row (push a new stage). |
|`Esc` |Pop the current stage. From root, closes the palette. |
|`↵` |Fire the selected row (or commit text). |

Everything else — pills, leaders, search reach, side preview, action menus — composes on top of these four.

! How sections compose

The palette has //layers// you can stack independently:

* ''Filters'' narrow the data set you're walking
* ''Reach'' widens search scope (current stage / whole tree)
* ''Search-in'' picks which fields the matcher reads
* ''Views'' switch between alternate trees of the same data
* ''Presets'' snapshot a layered configuration for one-keystroke recall

Each layer is a pill strip. Pills can be added (via leaders) and removed (DEL on a focused pill). No modal dialogs, no checkbox lists — just navigable pills.

